<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10770] Multiple @CompileStatic annotations don&apos;t combine extensions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10770</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When multiple levels of &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt; are present, various type-checking extensions can be specified independently, but the total list isn&apos;t aggregated:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
@CompileStatic(extensions = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;some-extension.groovy&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyClass {
  @CompileStatic(extensions = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;erroneously-skipped.groovy&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; myMethod() {}
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In such a case, all extensions should be applied collectively, inmost first. It might also make sense at some point to add some configuration to undo/disable other extensions, but for now composition is the piece that&apos;s not working correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I speculate that unified handling for &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;@TypeChecked&lt;/tt&gt; might be needed to make the various flavors all work together as expected by end users.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
